"Smithers: Sir, bad news from accounting, the economy's hit us pretty hard.<p>Mr. Burns: Tough times, huh? I've lived through twelve recessions, eight panics, and five years of <i>McKinleynomics</i>. I'll survive this.",
"Mr. Burns: You there! Fill this up with petroleum distillate. And revulcanize my tires, post haste!",
